{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1773050253,"nonce":"pTcaXie55BjpFYRM8RjgK7XOzxg=","title":"fix: disable ActiveStorage variant processor to suppress warning","message":"Rails logs this warning on every request:\n\n```\nGenerating image variants require the image_processing gem.\n```\n\nActiveStorage is used (`ParentItem` has `has_many_attached :files`) but image variants are never called. The `image_processing` gem is commented out in the Gemfile.\n\nFix: add `config.active_storage.variant_processor = :disabled` to all environment configs (development, test, production).","files":null}]}